Joseph Olaoluwa LG Electronics has upgraded its Free Wash Centre in Ogba, Ikeja, Lagos, with new sets of commercial washers and dryers for efficient free service delivery to families in the community and beyond. At a ceremony in Ikeja, the company presented a new commercial washing machine, Giant C Pro, developed to add value to its customers. The free laundry service was officially launched in 2018. It was targeted at alleviating the shortage of water and power supply in the area, for residents to efficiently carry out their laundry activities. Head of Corporate Marketing Division, LG Electronics West Africa, Hari Elluru, said the upgrade would improve the living conditions, as well as support the daily washing needs of people in the area. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact:Â theeditor@punchng.com 